6Expr Simplify::visit(const LT *op, ExprInfo *bounds) {
7 ExprInfo a_bounds, b_bounds;
8 Expr a = mutate(op->a, &a_bounds);
9 Expr b = mutate(op->b, &b_bounds);
10
11 const int lanes = op->type.lanes();
12 Type ty = a.type();
13
14 if (truths.count(op)) {
15 return const_true(lanes);
16 } else if (falsehoods.count(op)) {
17 return const_false(lanes);
18 }
19
20 if (may_simplify(ty)) {
21
22 // Prove or disprove using bounds analysis
23 if (a_bounds.max_defined && b_bounds.min_defined && a_bounds.max < b_bounds.min) {
24 return const_true(lanes);
25 }
26
27 if (a_bounds.min_defined && b_bounds.max_defined && a_bounds.min >= b_bounds.max) {
28 return const_false(lanes);
29 }
30
31 int lanes = op->type.lanes();
32 auto rewrite = IRMatcher::rewriter(IRMatcher::lt(a, b), op->type, ty);
33
34 // clang-format off
35 if (EVAL_IN_LAMBDA
36 (rewrite(c0 < c1, fold(c0 < c1)) ||
37 rewrite(x < x, false) ||
38 rewrite(x < ty.min(), false) ||
39 rewrite(ty.max() < x, false) ||
40
41 rewrite(max(x, y) < x, false) ||
42 rewrite(max(y, x) < x, false) ||
43 rewrite(x < min(x, y), false) ||
44 rewrite(x < min(y, x), false) ||
45
46 // From the simplifier synthesis project
47 rewrite((max(y, z) < min(x, y)), false) ||
48 rewrite((max(y, z) < min(y, x)), false) ||
49 rewrite((max(z, y) < min(x, y)), false) ||
50 rewrite((max(z, y) < min(y, x)), false) ||
51
52 // Comparisons of ramps and broadcasts. If the first
53 // and last lanes are provably < or >= the broadcast
54 // we can collapse the comparison.
55 (no_overflow(op->type) &&
56 (rewrite(ramp(x, c1, lanes) < broadcast(z, lanes), true,
57 can_prove(x + fold(max(0, c1 * (lanes - 1))) < z, this)) ||
58 rewrite(ramp(x, c1, lanes) < broadcast(z, lanes), false,
59 can_prove(x + fold(min(0, c1 * (lanes - 1))) >= z, this)) ||
60 rewrite(broadcast(z, lanes) < ramp(x, c1, lanes), true,
61 can_prove(z < x + fold(min(0, c1 * (lanes - 1))), this)) ||
62 rewrite(broadcast(z, lanes) < ramp(x, c1, lanes), false,
63 can_prove(z >= x + fold(max(0, c1 * (lanes - 1))), this))))
64 )) {
65 return rewrite.result;
66 }

340 // Comparison of stair-step functions. The basic transformation is:
341 // ((x + y)/c1)*c1 < x
342 // = (x + y) - (x + y) % c1 < x (when c1 > 0)
343 // = y - (x + y) % c1 < 0
344 // = y < (x + y) % c1
345 // This cancels x but duplicates y, so we only do it when y is a constant.
346
347 // A more general version with extra terms w and z
348 rewrite(((x + c0)/c1)*c1 + w < x + z, (w + c0) < ((x + c0) % c1) + z, c1 > 0) ||
349 rewrite(w + ((x + c0)/c1)*c1 < x + z, (w + c0) < ((x + c0) % c1) + z, c1 > 0) ||
350 rewrite(((x + c0)/c1)*c1 + w < z + x, (w + c0) < ((x + c0) % c1) + z, c1 > 0) ||
351 rewrite(w + ((x + c0)/c1)*c1 < z + x, (w + c0) < ((x + c0) % c1) + z, c1 > 0) ||
352 rewrite(x + z < ((x + c0)/c1)*c1 + w, ((x + c0) % c1) + z < w + c0, c1 > 0) ||
353 rewrite(x + z < w + ((x + c0)/c1)*c1, ((x + c0) % c1) + z < w + c0, c1 > 0) ||
354 rewrite(z + x < ((x + c0)/c1)*c1 + w, ((x + c0) % c1) + z < w + c0, c1 > 0) ||
355 rewrite(z + x < w + ((x + c0)/c1)*c1, ((x + c0) % c1) + z < w + c0, c1 > 0) ||
356
357 // w = 0
358 rewrite(((x + c0)/c1)*c1 < x + z, c0 < ((x + c0) % c1) + z, c1 > 0) ||
359 rewrite(((x + c0)/c1)*c1 < z + x, c0 < ((x + c0) % c1) + z, c1 > 0) ||
360 rewrite(x + z < ((x + c0)/c1)*c1, ((x + c0) % c1) + z < c0, c1 > 0) ||
361 rewrite(z + x < ((x + c0)/c1)*c1, ((x + c0) % c1) + z < c0, c1 > 0) ||
362
363 // z = 0
364 rewrite(((x + c0)/c1)*c1 + w < x, (w + c0) < ((x + c0) % c1), c1 > 0) ||

489 // Comparison of aligned ramps can simplify to a comparison of the base
490 rewrite(ramp(x * c3 + c2, c1, lanes) < broadcast(z * c0, lanes),
491 broadcast(x * fold(c3/c0) + fold(c2/c0) < z, lanes),

499 c1 * (lanes - 1) < c0 &&
500 c1 * (lanes - 1) >= 0)
501 ))) {
502 return mutate(rewrite.result, bounds);
503 }

505 }

507 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
508 return op;
509 } else {
510 return LT::make(a, b);

514// The other comparison operators redirect to the less-than operator
515Expr Simplify::visit(const LE *op, ExprInfo *bounds) {
516 if (!may_simplify(op->a.type())) {
517 Expr a = mutate(op->a, nullptr);
518 Expr b = mutate(op->b, nullptr);
519 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
520 return op;
521 } else {
522 return LE::make(a, b);
523 }
524 }
525
526 Expr mutated = mutate(!(op->b < op->a), bounds);
527 if (const LE *le = mutated.as<LE>()) {
528 if (le->a.same_as(op->a) && le->b.same_as(op->b)) {
529 return op;
530 }
531 }
532 return mutated;
533}
